text: John Stewart (c.1723–81), of York Buildings, Buckingham Street, London and Mitcham, Surrey, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of Great Britain for Arundel 13 May 1771 – 1774. ==References== Category:1720s births Category:1781 deaths Category:18th-century English people Category:People from Westminster Category:People from Mitcham Category:Members of the Parliament of Great Britain for English constituencies Category:British MPs 1768–1774
